# [[.NameTitle]] — Qorven App Bundle

Scaffolded by `qorven agent init`. Builds a self-contained IIFE bundle that installs into a running Qorven host.

## Project layout

```
src/index.tsx      — App entry point (JSX, uses window.__QorvenUI + window.__QorvenApp)
qorven-app.d.ts    — TypeScript declarations for Qorven host globals (do not edit)
vite.config.ts     — Vite IIFE build config
tsconfig.json      — TypeScript config
frontend/          — Build output (bundle.js lands here after `npm run build`)
```

## Development workflow

```bash
npm install
npm run build       # → frontend/bundle.js
```

Install the built bundle into a running Qorven instance:

```bash
# Via the Qorven CLI:
qorven app install --path /path/to/this/dir

# Or via the API:
curl -X POST http://localhost:4200/api/v1/apps \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{"path": "/path/to/this/dir"}'
```

## Available globals

Inside your `src/index.tsx`, two host globals are available:

**`window.__QorvenApp`** — host utilities
- `React` — the host's React instance (same version as the host)
- `request(path, init?)` — authenticated fetch against the Qorven API
- `getToken()` — returns the current auth token
- `register(app)` — register your pages/tabs with the host router

**`window.__QorvenUI`** — Qorven's Metronic component library
- All components: `Button`, `Card`, `Tabs`, `Dialog`, `Sheet`, `Input`, `Badge`, and 25+ more
- `cn(...classes)` — Tailwind class merging utility
- `icons` — full `lucide-react` icon namespace
- `useCurrentUser()` — React hook: current authenticated user
- `useActiveSoul()` — React hook: currently open Qorven soul
- `useWsConnected()` — React hook: WebSocket connection state

## Type checking

```bash
npm run typecheck
```

TypeScript declarations for all globals are in `qorven-app.d.ts` (generated — do not edit).
